sections.Quotes:
{{Quote|I know I broke my oath. I know I'm a deserter.|[[Will]]|Winter is Coming}}
{{Dialogue a-b-a|Greatjon Umber|I will lead the van or I will take my men and march them home.|Robb Stark|You are welcome to do so, Lord Umber. And when I am done with the Lannisters, I will march back North, root you out of your keep, and hang you for an oathbreaker.|'''Oathbreaker''', is it!? I will not sit here and swallow insults from a boy so green he pisses grass!|Greatjon is infuriated when accused of oathbreaking|Baelor}}
{{Dialogue a-b|Catelyn Stark|You swore an oath to my father.|Walder Frey|Oh, yes.  I said some words...|[[Walder Frey]] reveals what he thinks of his oath of loyalty to the Tullys|Baelor}}
{{Quote|Some men take their oaths more seriously than others.|Catelyn Stark|The Pointy End}}
{{Quote|My sword is yours, in victory and defeat, from this day until my last day.|Theon Greyjoy swears an oath, that he would eventually break, to Robb Stark |Fire and Blood}}
{{Dialogue a-b-a-b-a|Jorah Mormont|You can go, you can't have the eggs.|Viserys Targaryen|You swore an oath to me. Does loyalty mean nothing to you?|It means ''everything'' to me.|Yet here you stand|Yet here I stand|Jorah committing a wilful act of oathbreaking|A Golden Crown}}
